race.comment: SASS (7) switched from a top Sydney stable and progressed nicely last time out to finish just 0.8 lengths from the winner over 1300m. She's sure to have come on from that and is nicely placed to find winning ways. JUELENE (5) maps well and is busting to win. Will be right in it if she puts her best foot forward. JUST ALBERT (1) went close at Tatura (Victoria) first-up and then switched barns on a 25-day return and looked a run short here as favourite. He's right up to this and has to be seriously considered. GOOD ONYA DARL (4) is a former Victorian who presents fourth up off a 42-day freshen. Has the rail and the top hoop and some key gear changes. The betting should provide the best guide with her.
